<td style=" color:#000000; font-size:12pt; background-color:#FFFFFF; font-family:arial; bLabel:main; bEditID:r3st1;" tEditID="c1r2" locked="0" aEditID="c1r2" >
<![CDATA[<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 12pt;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><font size="2">Dear&nbsp;</font><font size="2">{!Contact.FirstName}</font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 18.399999618530273px;">Hope you are enjoying your summer so far and congratulations on being appointed as a Logistics Officer.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><b>What you should know about payment for your role:</b></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">You have been assigned a 64 day role; start date is the 7 July and end date is 3 October. Total salary for this role is £4000.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">You will be paid on a monthly basis from July to October, with a total of three payments constituting your salary for the role. Tax and NI deduction will be made from each monthly payment. See below.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><b>The amounts are calculated on the basis that you will work all days required to carry out your role; any days that you are absent will be deducted from your pay at the daily rate (£62.50) unless agreed with your line manager.</b><o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Please find your payment schedule below for your work with us on the NCS with The Challenge programme.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Payment 1: Payroll date 29 July<o:p></o:p></font></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Pay period is from 7 July to 31st July. Maximum total number of days worked is 19 days (7-11 July, 14-18 July, 21-22 July, 23-25 July, 28-31 July).<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Gross pay for this pay period will be £1187.50 which is subject to Tax and NI contributions.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Payment 2: Payroll Date 27 August<o:p></o:p></font></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Pay period is from 1 August to 31 August.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Maximum number of days worked is 22 days (1 August, 4-8 August, 11-15 August, 18-19 August, 20-22 August, 25-29 August, 31 August).<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Gross pay for this pay period will be £1375 which is subject to Tax and NI contributions.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Payment 3: Payroll Date 23 September<o:p></o:p></font></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Pay period is from 1 September to 3 October.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Maximum number of days worked is 23 days (1 September, 4-8 September, 11-15 September, 18-22 September, 25-29 September, 2-3 October).<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Gross pay for this pay period will be £1437.50 which is subject to Tax and NI contributions.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">You will receive your payslip via your personal email on the payroll dates listed above.<o:p></o:p></font></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Pension<o:p></o:p></font></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Due to new auto-enrolment legislation, employees of The Challenge, including summer staff, will be automatically enrolled in a workplace pension scheme. This is a way of saving for your retirement that's arranged by your employer. This affects staff who earn more than £473 per month and are aged between 22 and state pension age. You will see your pension contributions on your payslip. For further information, please go to www.gov.uk/workplace-pensions.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Further communications, including how to opt out, will be sent to you in September where we will start to process all summer staff for auto-enrolment. At that point, if you would like to opt out of the pension scheme, you will need an opt-out form from The People's Pension, which you can get from and then return to by emailing thepeoplespension@bandce.co.uk. Staff will have a one month opt-out period: this begins from the day the administration for their becoming a member is complete, i.e. one month from the date of enrolment, which will not take place until September.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">&nbsp;</font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 12pt;"></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Any questions let us know!<o:p></o:p></font></span></p><div><span style="line-height: 18.399999618530273px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></span></div>]]></td>
</tr>
